data.body:
**Steps to reproduce:**
1. Install MonoGame for Windows using the (as of now latest) 3.6.0.1379 installer.
1. Create a new DesktopGL project using the Visual Studio template.
1. Add a new sprite font to the content project. No need to modify the file.
1. Load the font in `Game1`:
```cs
protected override void LoadContent()
{
    spriteBatch = new SpriteBatch(GraphicsDevice);
    font = Content.Load<SpriteFont>("Font");
}
```
5. Draw some text using it:
```cs
protected override void Draw(GameTime gameTime)
{
    GraphicsDevice.Clear(Color.CornflowerBlue);
    spriteBatch.Begin();
    spriteBatch.DrawString(font, "Hello world", new Vector2(16, 16), Color.White);
    spriteBatch.End();

    base.Draw(gameTime);
}
```

No text appears. However, using the 3.6.0.1365 installer and later framework DLL builds, I narrowed it down to 1365 being the last working version and 1366 the first failing. This build contains #5121 and #5139, so either has caused the regression (could be related to @mrhelmut's comment in #5121?).
